(41, 12, 29, 46, 8, 4, 4, 'The Lord our God is one Lord', 'Unity of God in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the affirmation of monotheism in both passages. Mark emphasizes the oneness of God, while 1 Corinthians asserts that there is none other God but one.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 12, 29, 65, 1, 25, 25, 'The Lord our God is one Lord', 'Unity of God in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s singularity and majesty. Mark emphasizes the oneness of God, while Jude acknowledges God''s wisdom and power, reinforcing the concept of one divine authority.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
